      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CURADH (9) added to a string of placings when runner-up from the second line here two back before he led and kept going for a well-deserved win by close to 6m at the latest appearance at Northam. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but with even luck he could strike again. DIAMOND WORLD (3) has come from tougher barriers to place in his last two outings, the latest at this circuit and distance when he was drawn on the back row. Should enjoy an economical run from this draw so could break through. MAJOR DISCO (8) draws wide but has yet to miss a place this time in so is hard to knock. SHEER ROCK LADY (10) showed improvement for fourth last week and could progress further third-up.",
